,Recommended,312210,20812814,"Posted: 28 January, 2016",all,Trilaac,"Well,after readina lot of the reviews, I decided to give this game a go anyway.So glad that I did.The world is fairly open, insofar as it is a large worldbox. There's the ground, and hills, valleys, trees, buildings, tunnels, and the world extends out to the horizons in 4 directions (although you do hit the invisible wall at the edge).There are no objectives per-se. You simply need to survive. You can collect resources (mainly via harvester dotted around the world that require hacking to activate and control). You play a drone robot, so power generation and consumption is everything. I found the fastest way was to collect solar panels from the farms and capacitors from various locations, then stand still for a while to charge before moving off.Always keeping a watchful eye on the automated drones gives the game a certain edge, especially at night and when you're building structures. I build a small tower, and was standing at the top adding a roof when a drone walked into the bottom and exploded.Needless to say, it took out a corner of the building and the whole thing fell down, but you take no damage from falling so dont die.No, that comes in the form of hunter bots with shotguns that kill you in 2 shots.Overall, in my opinion, a nice game. It contains elements I enjoy: survival, open world, freebuild of tools, weapons and structures, achievments (there are Steam ones as well as in game for solo and multi play), and most importantly, it's always recieving updates. Always small, but they are always fixing a bug or adding a new featre, which is great."
