76561198027415967,Recommended,312210,30021116,Posted: 18 February,all,Kygeir,"This will be my very first review, so let me begin by saying that I'm seeing a whole lot of whining and b!tching about this game from reviewers who bought it knowing it's state of development. It's early access. Anyone who's bought an early access title before should know what that entails.If you don't have the patience for long waits then you have no buisiness buying this or any other early access title. Just because you pay for an incomplete product (and knowingly doing so) does not mean they are required to build a game on YOUR acceptable time frame. This game (as far as I'm aware of) is being built by one man. Not a small crew, but one man. Make your choice of purchase while being aware of this.Now. Lets get to the facts of this game and clear up some of the half truths and misleading information.First, yes this game has been in development for a while now. And yes it's still in an Alpha state. What does this mean for you? If you purchase this as is then you will be getting a game that's missing a lot, and likely become very bugy from time to time. Despite this, there are still a great many things to do for someone who is willing to learn without having their hand held like it was when they played WoW.Next, I've seen reviews saying that there is no tutorial, this is false. There is a playable tutorial that will show you the very basics of this game without holding your little WoW hand and telling you every little thing about the game.Now, about the updates, yes they are few and far between. Apparently people are still under the impression that one person, that one man, is required to release updates every week or hold their hand and take time away from what is most likely his real world life, job, and family to tell each and every one of them (personally, as they are special little snow flakes) what's going on and when things will be done. While I agree that his lack of communication is very unprofessional, again, this is one man who likely has a life. Like a few of us. And this is most likely his first attempt at build and selling a game. Keep this in mind before purchasing.I've also seen reviews stating that there is no new content. This is very much false. While some of these reviews are old enough to have somewhat of an excuse, I've actually seen newer reviews claiming this. Again, it's false. This game was released bare bones. There was almost nothing to it. There has been a significant amount of small content added that most would likely miss while they were busying wiping their eyes and lamenting on how they missed the good old handholding days of WoW when they'd get into trouble with their Pally and just bubble and Hearth. And a little complaining got all the drop rates adjusted to drop for them. I know. You are upset there is no bubble and hearth for when you are about to die and you are upset that you actually have to look for parts to build a decent gun instead of handing you a nuke. Yes, it's very sad, but you will live. But in all seriousness, there are a lot of items that I've heard about that I've not even found yet myself. Also, the last update just released a new area that appears to be an instanced zone that will have something to do with the upcoming storyline. So to finish this story, yes, there is new content. Yes, there are new things to do. The real problem is people not satisfied with how far apart the updates are. Again, if you don't have the patience for it then don't buy this game.I've also seen reviews about the graphics and gameplay saying they have not recieved any updates or improvements. This is, again, false. The AI had a big overhaul. The spawning system recieved a very big overhaul. There is no longer Enemies walking through walls, or standing at the base of the building that you are bravely cowering on waiting for them to kill eachother so you can escape. I know, you are angry that he took away your exploit and you now have to fight. You're♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥that you now have to worry about the enemy jumping up to your floor and spray painting your oily parts all over the wall from a close range shottyng  blast. Yes, it's sad.As for the graphics and optimization, yes, they can use a tweaking, but they have been tweaked already. I was originally getting around 12-16 ish fps. After the recent update I now get around 20-40 ish fps. On a 4 year old laptop running a 2.4 cpu, 8 gigs of ram, and a GTX 840m. I feel pretty certain that your gaming rig will likely do better.To finish up this little book I'll close with this: If you're not a spoiled little manchild missing your WoW days of having everything handed to your little Alliance pally and can actually LEARN to play something new that ISN'T finished yet and are capable of understanding that concept then you MIGHT just like this game. It's not for everyone. But if you have the maturity to understand that not everything has to be Witcher 3 quality just because you demand it, then you just might enjoy this for what it is. It's different. It's going to be slow and watching the growth could be enjoyable.If you're like me and have several early access titles (even the ones that were abandeoned) and the HUGE purchase price of 15 dollars won't make mommy and daddy so angry that they beat you, then you might want to get this. Worst case scenario, you lose the price of a fast food meal. Yeah, I know, it breaks the bank. Ouch. Sooo bad. Mommy will be sooo angry. Best case scenario, you actually enjoy it. Up to you to decide whether or not the risk of the game folding is worth it to you. Only you can decide this. Or mommy."
76561198089599691,Not Recommended,312210,17960715,"Posted: 9 September, 2015",all,Chibineko,"I was very disapointed with this game, to say the least. I wasn't expecting too much, but even then it failed to deliver.tl/dr; the combat is probably the worst part of the game, and in a survival game like this, that's a huge dealbreaker.The best thing about this game I can say is probably weapon crafting. While it's a pain early on, you could probably make some pretty nice weapons later on. I say probably, because I've never actually lasted longer than a few minutes, so I've never gotten to experiment with the weapon crafting.The enemies range from either absurdly stupid to absurdly powerful. There are ""creeper bots"" (they walk up to you and explode) but they're hardly a threat. I don't think I've even been damaged by one of them. There are Hive Bots, which are small, flying robots that swarm near their hives, but they are easily avoided. The real threat are ""Hunters"" I believe they are called. They spawn randomly and just wander around until you get near. And once they have locked on to you, you might as well be dead. They can kill you in about 2 shots and don't ever seem to miss. AND they travel in groups most of the time, spawning quiet frequently. Maybe they would be easy to kill with a decent weapon, but finding a gun isn't so simple. You usually find PARTS of weapons scattered through the world that you can craft together, but finding all of the essential parts takes awhile, and even if you complete a weapon, ammo is scarce. Melee weapons are a joke, the exploding bots kill themselves, Hive bots can be easily avoided, and Hunters will destroy you the moment you get within range.Even if poor combat wasn't enough, the world in this game is just so empty. The only place of interest is the giant spire which sometimes (I stress the word SOMETIMES) has good equipment. There aren't any bosses, food isn't a concern, base building is crude and, in the end, pointless, hacking is slow, confusing, and again, pointless. In the end, there just is nothing to do in this game."
