76561198135546385,Recommended,312210,19058996,"Posted: 13 November, 2015",all,Space Guy,"(NOTE: This review was made on an IPad. If it looks funky, that's why.)So, for those of you who want a quick answer, yes, get this game. You will (most likely) not regret it.Now for the more detailed analysis; this game, in its current state, is pretty dang fun. I've fiddled around with all the games major selling points and am pretty satisfied. For example, most survival games have guns that are pre-made and can't be modified aside from, for example, throwing a scope or silencer on it. TFD features weapons that can be modified and upgraded using gun parts you loot from the world. This makes acquiring a weapon pretty hard early on (though you can occasionally find an assembled weapon), but it also opens up many possibilities for your arsenal. Don't like the slide on your pistol? Simply switch it out with another, possibly better, slide. Want to decrease the weight of your weapon? Switch out the handle, shave off a little extra weight. And there's plenty more you can do with this, believe me. There is also a base construction system in place. It can be a little finicky at times, but all over all it's pretty easy to build yourself a structure, granted you get the resources to build it out of. Speaking of which, there is a hacking mechanic involved. I say this now because scattered around the map are harvesters that can be hacked to collect resources for you. Despite what other reviews are saying, it's incredibly easy to hack something. There is a bit of a command prompt, but all you need to do to hack a machine is to type in two commands; one right after the other. That's it. You can hack anything that moves (aside from players, of course). The enemies are particularly hard to deal with, but running away from them is a pretty easy thing to do until you have a gun and ammo. And looting, despite what people are saying, is relatively smooth. Not Rust smooth, mind you, but satisfactory none the less. The community is very small and the wiki is REALLY out of date, so you're going to be learning most of how to do things on your own. And the developers have not abandoned this game, they just released a bug-fix update not too long ago.All over all, TFD is pretty worth the money. Yes, you're going to run into a bug or two; it's an alpha, it's going to do that. This is a hard game. My advice, save often and keep going. For those who enjoy a challenge, this should provide what you seek.And the all-important rating: (drumroll) 9/10Thanks for reading."
