76561197995918203,Recommended,312210,13860760,"Posted: 5 January, 2015",all,Space Invader,"This is a survivial game set in a post apocalyptic setting where humanity has been wiped-out by machines.  You are an android and you must avoid or fight the robots that you encounter.Although you do not require food or water to survivel (you're a machine) - you will need weapons, ammo and supplies.There is an impressive home/base building system in this game.  You can build small shelters to massive installations (building system is similar to Rust).  The gathering of the building supplies is unique.  Instead of ""you"" spending time collecting wood, concrete, metal, etc - you find and program flying machines called ""Harvesters"" to do this for you.The enemy in this game are robots  that seek your destruction.  they come in a few different varieties.  One is a walking bomb.  Another is a flying swarm.  The other is essentially ""Terminator"".You spend a lot  of your time exploring and searching through the ruined buildings for useful stuff - and you have to really manage your weight/energy supply in this game.  The more loot you carry - the more energy you use to move.  If you run out of energy - you must wait for your supply to recharge.  this becomes a problem if there are robots coming after you.  The enemies are a real threat - you can be one-shotted by them.The most impressive part of this game is the structures you can build.  The downsize is that other than gun turrets and a power station - they are largely empty and only serve as protection against bots or other players (if play multi-player).  There really is no decorations or furniture - again you're a machine.Overall in the short time I have played it - i like what I saw.  I think this game has potential.  The map is decent size but not massive.  I could not see multi-player supporting more than 3-4 players on a server."
